text: Elena Ţurcan (born 11 June 1975) is a Moldovan former footballer who played as a midfielder. She has been a member of the Moldova women's national team. ==International career== Ţurcan capped for Moldova at senior level during the UEFA second categories of two FIFA Women's World Cup qualifiers (2003 and 2007). ==References== Category:1975 births Category:Living people Category:Women's association football midfielders Category:Moldovan women's footballers Category:People from Ștefan Vodă District Category:Moldova women's international footballers Category:Ryazan-VDV players Category:Gintra Universitetas players Category:Moldovan expatriate footballers Category:Moldovan expatriate sportspeople in Russia Category:Expatriate women's footballers in Russia Category:Moldovan expatriate sportspeople in Lithuania Category:Expatriate women's footballers in Lithuania
